P(X \geq c) \leq \frac{E[X]}/c
t
P(t X \geq c t) = P(e^{t X} \geq e^{c t}) \leq \frac{E[e^{t X}]}{c t} = \frac{M_X(t)}{c t}
t>0
X = \sum_i Y_i
\{Y_i\}
\{Y_i\}
M_X(t) = \prod_i M_{Y_i}(t)
\{X_i\}_{i=1}^n
M_X
P(\sum_i X_i \geq c) \leq \inf_{t >0} \frac{(M_X(t))^n}{c t}
